<subSubSection pageId="102" pageNumber="860" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="102.[791,1384,284,712]" pageId="102" pageNumber="860">
Previously separated in genus Baeodon, but this was later reduced to a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[792,917,371,396]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Rhogeessa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="102" pageNumber="860" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Rhogeessa</taxonomicName>
, based on bacular, external and skull morphology. Recent molecular studies using mtDNA and nDNA grouped this species with R. gracilisin a clade sister to all other congeners, reinforcing some morphological evidence that suggests these two species may be basal within the genus; they may be better isolated in genus Baeodon. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
